VCharulatha&#8217;s melodic modulation and nalinam in bowing was punctuated with imaginative phrasings in her solo versions of Kharaharapriya, Thodi and Saveri. The thani by Surendran (mridangam) and Murali (ghatam) was embedded with perceptive laya patterns pleasing to the ear.
